So I've downloaded the first episodes of this torrent to see what quality was like -> deleted immediately. Too much compression so not worth dowloading if you intend to watch this on a big screen. The show looks good though so I'll be looking for a much better source, which shouldn't be difficult at all.

The ripper/uploader screwed up the aspect ratio. They've manually changed it to 16:9 (widescreen) from its native 4:3 (fullscreen). As such, it looks noticeably squashed. Looks rather horrid. 

If you're watching the show on your PC, get VLC Media Player, play an episode and go to Video -> Aspect Ratio -> 4:3. Looks MUCH better.
Ok, looks like the aspect ratio problem is only present in the pilot.
